text:
Use keywords to search content on this website Search Use keywords to search content on this website NSWRL name women’s squad to start defence of state of origin title February 23, 2017 11:32am NSW Women’s Rugby League squad members Kezie Apps, Rebecca Riley, Allana Ferguson and Nakia Davis-Welsh. Picture by Scott Fletcher THE female rugby league players with a shot of defending their historic state of origin victory from last year were today named by New South Wales Rugby League. 
The 22 players will gather this weekend at Sydney Oluympic Park for a camp, the first session of the 2017 Women’s Pathways Program. 
Seven more sessions will be held between now and midyear, when the interstate challenge will be played on the weekend of July 21-23. 
Other players still have a chance to make the squad as coaching staff will watch the NSW women’s premiership and Tarsha Gale Cup for emerging talent. 
For the first time, the female Pathways Program will be directly aligned to the male Pathways program. NSW defeated Queensland for the first time in 17 years in 2016. Picture: Adam Taylor 
2017 NSW Women’s Interstate Challenge Pathways Squad 
Isabelle Kelly (Berkeley Vale Panthers) 
Jayme Fressard (Berkeley Vale Panthers) 
Vanessa Foliaki (Brisbane Easts Tigers) 
Allana Ferguson (Cronulla Caringbah)
